content:
When working within the FlexCard Designer, you may run into issues that require some troubleshooting to resolve. Before contacting support, consider these troubleshooting articles.

Update Remote Site Settings to Preview Your FlexCard: Grant access to your org domains to enable LWC features such as Preview. When spinning a new org or new installation, update the Tooling API calls necessary for LWC by including the URLs required in the Remote Site Settings page.

Update the FlexCard Object's Default Lightning Record Page to Access the FlexCard Designer: Update your org's default Lightning record page for the Omni UI Card object to Vlocity Card Designer. If you click on a FlexCard and see a record detail page instead of the FlexCard Designer, set the org's default Lightning record page to Vlocity Card Designer.

Fix Cyclic Redundancy When Embedding FlexCard Components: Check that components are not called multiple times when embedding components such as flyouts, Custom LWCs, and child FlexCards. If you add components that call themselves or call other components embedded inside components, it may create cyclic redundancy causing events to continuously fire in your browser.
